      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:49:8",
      "text": [
        " لَيْسَ لِلْمَرِيضِ أَنْ يُطَلِّقَ وَ لَهُ أَنْ يَتَزَوَّجَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazzal, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘It is not for the sick that he divorces but for him is that he can marry’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn Faddal from ibn Bukayr from Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One cannot divorce his wife in his illness but his marriage is permissible.’” "
        ]
      }
